[[div class="blockquote"]]
= **Incident XXXX.126834**
= Alice Springs, Northern Territory, Australia

[[include component:image-block | name=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Alice_Springs_Australia.jpg/640px-Alice_Springs_Australia.jpg | caption=Alice Springs. ]]

**03/07/2023**: Rio Tinto, a mining company, reports 8% lower productivity for the 2023 fiscal year. Managers claim employees are taking longer than average bathroom breaks.

**12/08/2023**: The Hot Topic, a sensationalist news tabloid, lampoons the poor construction of septic tanks in the region, citing 8 tanks that overflowed in the past 2 weeks. Site-84 sends Agent Murray to investigate.

**12/09/2023**: Agent Murray returns. During debriefing, Murray claims he met civilian F. Gordon in a restroom in his hotel's lobby, where they professed their love for each other. Influence from SCP-XXXX is suspected.

**15/09/2023**: Gordon is located and retrieved. During Operation Dehydration, Gordon's blood sample tests for a 45.56% concentration of SCP-XXXX.

**28/09/2023**: Surveillance cameras are set up in public restrooms throughout Alice Springs. [[footnote]] Due to the low population density of the Northern Territory, enactment of containment procedures in the region was not prioritised. [[/footnote]]

**26/10/2023**: 1,340 manifestations are observed over the past 4 weeks. Average constituent SCP-XXXX in affected subjects measures 42.44%. Site-84 is unable to accommodate all subjects and sustainably perform Operation Dehydration. 

[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Proposal**: Request for 500 more personnel to assist containment of SCP-XXXX.

**Status**: Accepted - //O-█//
[[/div]]

**12/11/2023**: 8 SCP-XXXX researchers, 85 field agents and 410 non-English-speaking D-Class personnel are transferred to Site-84. 

[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Proposal**: Enactment of Operation Dehydration in civilian homes. Civilians are exposed to a Class I Obedience cognitohazard to ensure compliance.

**Status**: Accepted - //Site 84 Ethics Committee Liaison//
[[/div]]

[[div class="blockquote"]]

= Incident.126834 - Preliminary research notes

Alright, I admit I might have objected a little too strongly against moving 15,000km across the globe into the middle of bumfuck nowhere. However, even ignoring the fact that the toilets here flush backwards, this place is pretty interesting. Because it's so remote, most of the drinking water comes from recycled sewerage. Yes, the people here are drinking their own piss, and because of SCP-XXXX, they piss a whole lot more than they drink.

Undoing this funky feedback loop could help my case for a promotion. I'll apologise to Director Moose when this is over.

[[>]]
//- Dr. Y. Nations//
[[/>]]

[[/div]]

**20/11/2023**: The UR-1-NE centrifuge at Site-84 is relocated to a civilian water treatment plant. Foundation staff are advised against entering any restroom when someone else is present. A replacement centrifuge is ordered.

**22/11/2023**: Concentration of SCP-XXXX in sewerage exceeds the filtration capacity of a single UR-1-NE centrifuge. 4 more centrifuges are ordered.

**01/12/2023**: Average constituent SCP-XXXX in affected subjects reaches 55.67%. Alice Springs is placed under quarantine. A cover story is provided, justifying the quarantine due to a COVID-19 outbreak in the town. 

**07/12/2023**: Field agents report that civilians are seeking out public restrooms, and are unwilling to urinate by themselves.

**14/12/2023**: Volume of SCP-XXXX exceeds storage capacity of Site-84. Excess SCP-XXXX is dumped into the surrounding desert.

**20/12/2023**: Agent Liu is compromised in a civilian bathroom, and she reveals the existence of the Foundation. Subjects involved are amnesticised.

**01/01/2024**: Average constituent SCP-XXXX in affected subjects reaches 63.44%. Subjects exceeding 70% constituent SCP-XXXX express reluctance to use a toilet without a capable conversation partner.

[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Proposal**: Civilians are exposed to a Class II Obedience cognitohazard to ensure compliance.

**Status**: Accepted - //Site 84 Ethics Commitee Liaison//
[[/div]]

**15/01/2024**: 5 UR-1-NE centrifuges arrive, and are installed in local water treatment facilities and Site-84. Filtration is capable of diverting 83% of SCP-XXXX from the town's main water supply.

**24/01/2024**: Excess dumping of SCP-XXXX in the surrounding desert has led to desert blooms outside of standard seasonal patterns, attracting non-native species.

**25/01/2024**: 13 children and 2 teachers collapse from heat stroke in an elementary school. Interruption of the manifestation was delayed due to staff shortages.

[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Proposal**: Request for 1,000 more personnel to enable neutralisation of SCP-XXXX.

**Status**: Rejected - //O-██//

**Reasoning**: Insufficient non-English-speaking D-Class. Proposal would compromise containment in other sites.
[[/div]]

**01/02/2024**: Average constituent SCP-XXXX in affected subjects reaches 67.22%. Subjects exceeding 85% constituent SCP-XXXX express reluctance to use a toilet without a capable conversation partner. 

[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Proposal**: Civilians are exposed to a Class III Obedience cognitohazard to ensure compliance.

**Status**: Rejected - //Site 84 Ethics Commitee Liaison//

**Reasoning**: Adverse health effects from medium-term exposure.
[[/div]]

**11/02/2024**: A civilian with 94.24% constituent SCP-XXXX refuses Operation Dehydration, and wets himself outside of a bathroom.

[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Proposal**: Request for 1000 more personnel to enable neutralisation of SCP-XXXX. English-speaking D-Class may be procured, provided they are administered Class DX amnestics targeting the Broca region of the frontal lobe, disabling speech production.

--Status: Rejected - //Site 84 Ethics Commitee Liaison//--

--Reasoning: Dismantling such fundamental neural pathways would risk reducing personnel to a vegetative state.--

**Status**: Accepted - //Overruled by O5 Council vote//
[[/div]]

**24/02/2024**: 120 field agents and 720 D-Class personnel are transferred to Site-84.

**01/03/2024**: Average constituent SCP-XXXX in affected subjects drops to 65.69%.

**12/02/2024**: Excess dumping of SCP-XXXX in the surrounding desert has led to the formation of quicksand deposits and toxic algal blooms.

**21/03/2024**: Multiple civilians protest against poor treatment. Firearm use is authorised to quell potential riots.

**01/04/2024**: Average constituent SCP-XXXX in affected subjects drops to 64.21%.

**10/04/2024**: A civilian with 99.34% constituent SCP-XXXX refuses Operation Dehydration. He is unable to relax his bladder muscles without a capable conversation partner. He expires after [REDACTED] from the water pressure.

**01/05/2024**: Average constituent SCP-XXXX in affected subjects drops to 63.01%. Cost of maintaining containment in Alice Springs exceeds $15,000,000 per month. O5 Council requests the research team to seek alternative methods to neutralise SCP-XXXX.

[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Proposal**: Disperse residents of Alice Springs to available Foundation facilities, and enact Operation Dehydration. This would be conducted piecemeal since the global on-site capacity for Operation Dehydration is 8,400 individuals. Cost for long-distance transport and Operation Dehydration of 36,000 people is estimated to be $70,000,000. 

**Status**: Pending

[[/div]]

[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Proposal**: Blood transfusion of all residents to artificially reduce constituent SCP-XXXX to 0.00%. 180,000L of blood is required. Process to procure this volume of blood is under development.

**Status**: Pending

[[/div]]

[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Proposal**: Withdraw containment operations in Alice Springs and quarantine indefinitely. 

**Status**: Denied - //Dr. Y. Nations//

**Reasoning**: Left unchecked, an estimated 5,184,000L of SCP-XXXX would be produced per day.

[[/div]]

**01/06/2024**: Average constituent SCP-XXXX in affected subjects drops to 61.96%. Excess dumping of SCP-XXXX has led to higher than average rainfall in the Northern Territory. Manifestations of SCP-XXXX are reported in other towns in the region.


[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Proposal**: Terminate all residents. Alice Springs provides little economic value.

**Status**: Pending
[[/div]]

[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Proposal**: Clone all residents with SCP-████. Repurpose the originals to D-Class personnel, and globally distribute them to Foundation facilities. Excess personnel are culled. This would help recoup the prior expenditure used for containment.

**Status**: Pending

[[/div]]

**25/06/2024**: Proposal to [REDACTED] is accepted. Operation Siccitas is drafted to implement the proposal, and Alice Springs is cleared of SCP-XXXX after three weeks.

**30/06/2024**: The SCP-XXXX research team is tasked with identifying population centres with a similar hydrological profile to Alice Springs. Those with prevalence of SCP-XXXX are designated as Exspes-Class, and Operation Siccitas is to be likewise implemented to ensure containment. 

[[/div]]

[[div class="blockquote"]]
= **Incident XXXX.201983**

= Bathroom, Nations Residence

Dr. Nations flushes his toilet after urinating. The toilet explodes, decimating both the bathroom and Dr. Nations. The following note is found in the rubble:

> CONGRATULATIONS ON YOUR PEE-RRHIC VICTORY. WE KNOW HUMANITY'S SECRETS. [[[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-7939 | WE ARE COMING]]].


